Average is an ambiguous term, but can assume	\newline
\textbf{Arithmetic Mean:}
\vspace{-1.0ex}
\begin{center}
	$\sum\limits^n	\frac{x_n}{n}$
\end{center}

\pause

Average is the expected value or central tendency of a distributionm like the	\newline
\textbf{Median:}
\vspace{-1.0ex}
\begin{center}
	$x_1	\ldots	x_{n/2}	\ldots	x_n$
		~~or~~
	$x_1	\ldots	\frac{x_{n/2-1} + x_{n/2+1}}{2}	\ldots	x_n$
\end{center}

\pause

\textbf{Geometric Mean:}
\begin{center}
	$\prod\limits^n	\sqrt[n]{x_n}$
		~~or~~
	$e^{\overline{log(x)}}$
\end{center}

Advantages and disadvantages make it context sensitive

